	"system": {
		"description": "<p>Kusunoki is a tall tree with waxy-looking leaves and the smell of camphor when crushed. In spring, it produces bunches of very small white fragrant flowers in bright green foliage. Passing steam through the pulverized wood and condensing the vapors will produce camphor, a waxy, colorless solid with a strong aroma. Camphor stimulates the body's nervous system and offers a cooling sensation that is both numbing and soothing.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Effect.</strong></em> When applied to a creature suffering from the [[/condition id=paralyzed]] condition, the topical liniment enables the creature to immediately repeat the saving throw they made against the condition.</p>",
